Description: Sailor Moon fights for justice in the name of the Moon and the mysterious Moon Princess. Along the way, she recruits other girls to be Sailor Scouts and join her fight against evil.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 10
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: This new, expanded edition delves deeper into the story of Amuro Ray, a teenage mechanic, and an  experimental defense suit who are in the middle of a space war.
Title: MOBILE SUIT GUNDAM: THE ORIGIN, VOL. 1
Author: Yoshikazu Yasuhiko and Hajime Yatate
Contributor: by Yoshikazu Yasuhiko and Hajime Yatate

Description: Maka, an arms expert, wants to turn the Soul Eater, her living scythe, into the ultimate weapon for Death.
Title: SOUL EATER, VOL. 13
Author: Atsushi Ohkubo

Description: Cross Academy has day and evening students, but the latter have a secret: they are vampires.
Title: VAMPIRE KNIGHT, VOL. 16
Author: Matsuri Hino

Description: Journey to Ikebukuro, a Japanese city with lots of unusual activity, including the Black Biker, who is rumored to be headless.
Title: DURARARA: SAIKA ARC, VOL. 1
Author: Ryohgo Narita

Description: Life in a high school filled with werewolves and vampires continues.
Title: ROSARIO+VAMPIRE SEASON II, VOL. 11
Author: Akihisa Ikeda

Description: Staz is a vampire obsessed with Japanese culture. When a young Japanese girl he befriends suddenly dies, Staz vows to restore her, especially since it will give him a chance to walk among humans.
Title: BLOOD LAD, VOL. 2
Author: Yuuki Kodama

Description: Yuma Tsukumo will stop at nothing to become the Duel Masters champion, but as a rank amateur, the odds are stacked against him. Luckily, he has a mysterious spirit named Astral to help him.
Title: YU-GI-OH! ZEXAL, VOL. 2
Author: Kazuki Takahashi

Description: This series is about grade-school boys who want to become professionals in the manga industry.
Title: BAKUMAN, VOL. 18
Author: Tsugumi Ohba

Description: Monkey D. Luffy and his motley crew of would-be pirates search for a legendary treasure called “One Piece.”
Title: ONE PIECE, VOL. 66
Author: Eiichiro Oda
